      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Derek Jeter was on first base when David Justice rapped a grounder to first baseman John Olerud in the first inning. Olerud fired the ball to Alex Rodriguez at second base and Jeter slid in hard on the Seattle shortstop and his close friend.</p>
        <p>After Rodriguez completed the double play, he waved his finger back and forth to jokingly say that Jeter should not have slid toward him. Rodriguez then playfully tossed a handful of dirt on Jeter.</p>
        <p>Jack Curry</p>
        <p>2000 PLAYOFFS: YANKEES NOTEBOOK</p>
      </block>
